WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.760
Psalm 106-115.

00:16.710 --> 00:18.560
The Book of Psalms.

00:18.800 --> 00:20.520
King James Version.

00:20.880 --> 00:23.380
Psalm 106.

00:23.960 --> 00:25.260
Praise ye the LORD!

00:25.580 --> 00:28.240
O give thanks unto the LORD!

00:28.240 --> 00:32.900
For he is good, for his mercy endureth forever.

00:34.140 --> 00:36.840
Who can utter the mighty acts of the LORD?

00:37.600 --> 00:40.180
Who can show forth all his praise?

00:41.200 --> 00:43.520
Blessed are they that keep judgment,

00:44.260 --> 00:47.360
And he that doeth righteousness at all times.

00:48.280 --> 00:53.720
Remember me, O LORD, with the favor that thou bearest unto thy people.

00:54.220 --> 00:56.680
O visit me with thy salvation,

00:56.680 --> 01:00.600
That I may see the good of thy chosen,

01:01.160 --> 01:04.660
That I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation,

01:05.080 --> 01:07.920
That I may glory with thine inheritance.

01:09.040 --> 01:11.100
We have sinned with our fathers,

01:11.460 --> 01:13.300
We have committed iniquity,

01:13.860 --> 01:15.680
We have done wickedly.

01:16.460 --> 01:19.720
Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt,

01:20.100 --> 01:23.460
They remembered not the multitude of thy mercies,

01:23.460 --> 01:27.540
But provoked him at the sea, even at the Red Sea.

01:28.400 --> 01:32.540
Nevertheless, he saved them for his name's sake,

01:33.160 --> 01:36.440
That he might make his mighty power to be known.

01:37.540 --> 01:41.880
He rebuked the Red Sea also, and it was dried up,

01:42.120 --> 01:46.240
So he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.

01:46.820 --> 01:51.080
And he saved them from the hand of him that hated them,

01:51.080 --> 01:55.000
And redeemed them from the hand of the enemy,

01:56.500 --> 01:58.760
And the waters covered their enemies.

02:00.440 --> 02:02.740
There was not one of them left,

02:03.480 --> 02:07.620
Then believed they his words, they sang his praise,

02:08.680 --> 02:10.600
They soon forgot his works,

02:11.200 --> 02:13.820
They waited not for his counsel,

02:14.180 --> 02:16.720
But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness,

02:17.160 --> 02:19.120
And tempted God in the desert,

02:19.820 --> 02:21.840
And he gave them their request,

02:22.660 --> 02:25.380
But sent leanness into their soul,

02:25.960 --> 02:28.520
They envied Moses also in the camp,

02:28.860 --> 02:31.020
And Aaron the saint of the Lord.

02:32.060 --> 02:35.300
The earth opened, and swallowed up Dathan,

02:35.660 --> 02:37.700
And covered the company of Abiram,

02:38.260 --> 02:40.620
And a fire was kindled in their company,

02:41.140 --> 02:43.840
The flame burned up the wicked.

02:44.920 --> 02:46.840
They made a calf in Horeb,

02:46.840 --> 02:49.400
And worshipped the molten image,

02:50.200 --> 02:52.040
Thus they changed their glory,

02:52.440 --> 02:55.720
Into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass,

02:56.220 --> 02:58.280
They forgot God their Saviour,

02:59.100 --> 03:01.680
Which had done great things in Egypt,

03:02.060 --> 03:04.700
Wondrous works in the land of Ham,

03:05.060 --> 03:07.740
And terrible things by the Red Sea.

03:08.620 --> 03:11.580
Therefore he said that he would destroy them,

03:12.060 --> 03:15.900
Had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach,

03:15.900 --> 03:19.800
To turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.

03:20.460 --> 03:23.580
Yea, they despised the pleasant land,

03:23.820 --> 03:25.620
They believed not his word,

03:26.240 --> 03:27.940
But murmured in their tents,

03:28.040 --> 03:30.900
And hearkened not unto the voice of the Lord.

03:31.540 --> 03:33.800
Therefore he lifted up his hand against them,

03:34.020 --> 03:36.080
To overthrow them in the wilderness,

03:36.460 --> 03:40.660
To overthrow their seed also among the nations,

03:40.760 --> 03:42.700
And to scatter them in the lands.

03:43.480 --> 03:46.800
They joined themselves also unto Balpior,

03:47.420 --> 03:49.640
And ate the sacrifices of the dead,

03:50.000 --> 03:53.620
Thus they provoked him to anger with their inventions,

03:54.340 --> 03:57.020
And the plague break in upon them,

03:57.380 --> 04:00.700
Then stood up Phineas, and executed judgment,

04:01.240 --> 04:02.900
And so the plague was stayed,

04:03.320 --> 04:05.960
And that was counted unto him for righteousness,

04:06.240 --> 04:08.780
Unto all generations for evermore.

04:09.700 --> 04:13.760
They angered him also at the waters of Strife,

04:14.480 --> 04:17.230
So that it went ill with Moses for their sakes,

04:18.000 --> 04:20.580
Because they provoked his spirit,

04:20.940 --> 04:24.460
So that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.

04:25.520 --> 04:29.800
They did not destroy the nations concerning whom the Lord commanded them,

04:30.080 --> 04:32.500
But were mingled among the heathen,

04:32.680 --> 04:34.080
And learned their works,

04:34.460 --> 04:36.340
And they served their idols,

04:36.580 --> 04:38.260
Which were a snare unto them,

04:38.260 --> 04:42.840
Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,

04:43.100 --> 04:44.660
And shed innocent blood,

04:44.960 --> 04:47.940
Even the blood of their sons and of their daughters,

04:48.240 --> 04:51.500
Whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan,

04:52.580 --> 04:54.720
And the land was polluted with blood,

04:55.660 --> 04:58.920
Thus were they defiled with their own works,

04:59.760 --> 05:03.080
And went a-whoring with their own inventions.

05:04.040 --> 05:07.800
Therefore was the wrath of the Lord kindled against his people,

05:07.800 --> 05:10.920
In so much that he abhorred his own inheritance,

05:11.820 --> 05:15.120
And he gave them into the hand of the heathen,

05:15.460 --> 05:18.960
And they that hated them ruled over them,

05:19.340 --> 05:21.440
Their enemies also oppressed them,

05:21.980 --> 05:25.400
And they were brought into subjection under their hand.

05:26.320 --> 05:28.780
Many times did he deliver them,

05:28.920 --> 05:31.220
But they provoked him with their counsel,

05:31.720 --> 05:34.260
And were brought low for their iniquity.

05:35.260 --> 05:37.600
Nevertheless he regarded their affliction,

05:37.600 --> 05:39.380
When he heard their cry,

05:39.900 --> 05:42.220
And he remembered for them his covenant,

05:42.760 --> 05:46.300
And repented according to the multitude of his mercies.

05:47.540 --> 05:53.020
He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.

05:53.720 --> 05:55.520
Save us, O Lord our God,

05:56.240 --> 05:59.420
And gather us from among the heathen,

05:59.640 --> 06:01.500
To give thanks unto thy holy name,

06:01.560 --> 06:03.600
And to triumph in thy praise.

06:04.620 --> 06:07.540
Blessed be the Lord God of Israel,

06:07.740 --> 06:10.020
From everlasting to everlasting,

06:10.880 --> 06:13.260
And let all the people say Amen,

06:14.060 --> 06:15.380
Praise ye the Lord.

06:17.640 --> 06:19.080
Psalm 107

06:19.600 --> 06:22.020
O give thanks unto the Lord,

06:22.120 --> 06:23.260
For he is good,

06:23.820 --> 06:26.640
For his mercy endureth for ever.

06:27.460 --> 06:29.620
Let the redeemed of the Lord say so,

06:30.520 --> 06:33.480
Whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy,

06:34.120 --> 06:36.260
And gathered them out of the lands,

06:36.360 --> 06:37.240
From the east,

06:37.720 --> 06:38.840
And from the west,

06:39.160 --> 06:39.920
From the north,

06:39.960 --> 06:41.280
And from the south.

06:42.240 --> 06:45.420
They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way,

06:45.820 --> 06:48.220
They found no city to dwell in,

06:48.500 --> 06:49.840
Hungry and thirsty,

06:50.300 --> 06:52.180
Their soul fainted in them.

06:52.700 --> 06:55.340
Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble,

06:55.420 --> 06:58.400
And he delivered them out of their distresses.

06:59.360 --> 07:02.340
And he led them forth by the right way,

07:02.920 --> 07:06.720
That they might go to a city of habitation.

07:07.980 --> 07:11.120
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

07:11.680 --> 07:15.220
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

07:16.000 --> 07:18.960
For he satisfieth the longing soul,

07:19.440 --> 07:22.620
And filleth the hungry soul with goodness.

07:24.200 --> 07:26.240
Such as sit in darkness,

07:26.400 --> 07:27.860
And in the shadow of death,

07:28.300 --> 07:30.580
Being bound in affliction and iron,

07:30.580 --> 07:33.860
Because they rebelled against the words of God,

07:34.560 --> 07:37.500
And condemned the council of the Most High.

07:38.100 --> 07:40.760
Therefore he brought down their heart with labor,

07:41.380 --> 07:42.720
They fell down,

07:43.120 --> 07:44.720
And there was none to help.

07:45.680 --> 07:47.780
Then they cried unto the Lord in their trouble,

07:47.900 --> 07:50.260
And he saved them out of their distresses.

07:51.780 --> 07:53.980
He brought them out of darkness,

07:54.480 --> 07:55.860
And the shadow of death,

07:56.180 --> 07:58.560
And break their bands in sunder.

07:59.260 --> 08:02.880
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

08:03.600 --> 08:07.220
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

08:08.060 --> 08:10.860
For he hath broken the gates of brass,

08:11.420 --> 08:14.140
And cut the bars of iron and sunder.

08:15.260 --> 08:17.460
Fools, because of their transgression,

08:17.560 --> 08:20.620
And because of their iniquities, are afflicted,

08:20.900 --> 08:24.100
Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat,

08:24.640 --> 08:27.720
And they draw near unto the gates of death.

08:28.560 --> 08:31.420
Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble,

08:31.660 --> 08:34.320
And he saveth them out of their distresses.

08:34.560 --> 08:36.960
He sent his word, and healed them,

08:37.140 --> 08:39.880
And delivered them from their destructions.

08:40.560 --> 08:44.460
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

08:45.060 --> 08:48.160
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

08:48.760 --> 08:52.200
And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving,

08:52.800 --> 08:55.780
And declare his works with rejoicing.

08:56.290 --> 08:59.120
They that go down to the sea in ships,

08:59.560 --> 09:01.700
That do business in the great waters,

09:02.900 --> 09:05.180
These see the works of the Lord,

09:05.780 --> 09:07.760
And his wonders in the deep.

09:08.880 --> 09:12.520
For he commandeth and raiseth the stormy wind,

09:12.900 --> 09:15.300
Which lifteth up the waves thereof.

09:16.080 --> 09:17.920
They mount up to the heaven.

09:18.880 --> 09:21.340
They go down again to the depths,

09:21.560 --> 09:24.800
Their soul is melted because of trouble.

09:24.800 --> 09:29.580
They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man,

09:29.900 --> 09:31.700
And are at their wit's end.

09:32.400 --> 09:34.820
Then they cry unto the Lord in their trouble,

09:34.980 --> 09:37.360
And he bringeth them out of their distresses.

09:38.360 --> 09:40.540
He maketh the storm a calm,

09:41.000 --> 09:43.740
So that the waves thereof are still.

09:45.080 --> 09:47.740
Then they are glad because they be quiet.

09:48.780 --> 09:52.320
So he bringeth them unto their desired haven.

09:52.880 --> 09:56.600
O that men would praise the Lord for his goodness,

09:57.200 --> 10:00.760
And for his wonderful works to the children of men,

10:01.320 --> 10:05.120
Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people,

10:05.580 --> 10:08.900
And praise him in the assembly of the elders.

10:09.780 --> 10:11.880
He turneth rivers into a wilderness,

10:12.760 --> 10:15.720
And the water springs into dry ground,

10:16.280 --> 10:18.860
A fruitful land into barrenness.

10:19.380 --> 10:21.880
For the wickedness of them that dwell therein,

10:21.880 --> 10:25.860
He turneth the wilderness into a standing water,

10:26.140 --> 10:28.760
And dry ground into water springs.

10:29.980 --> 10:32.360
And there he maketh the hungry to dwell,

10:32.900 --> 10:35.900
That they may prepare a city for habitation,

10:36.540 --> 10:39.480
And sow the fields and plant vineyards,

10:39.820 --> 10:42.100
Which may yield fruits of increase.

10:43.080 --> 10:45.000
He blesseth them also,

10:45.440 --> 10:47.880
So that they are multiplied greatly,

10:48.360 --> 10:51.100
And suffereth not their cattle to decrease.

10:51.660 --> 10:53.960
Again they are minnished,

10:54.220 --> 10:56.140
And brought low through oppression,

10:56.600 --> 10:57.960
Affliction and sorrow.

10:58.740 --> 11:01.600
He poureth contempt upon princes,

11:02.320 --> 11:04.980
And causeth them to wander in the wilderness

11:04.980 --> 11:06.500
Where there is no way.

11:07.080 --> 11:10.520
Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction,

11:11.000 --> 11:13.960
And maketh him families like a flock.

11:14.800 --> 11:17.340
The righteous shall see it and rejoice,

11:17.840 --> 11:20.940
And all iniquity shall stop her mouth.

11:21.800 --> 11:25.660
Whoso is wise and will observe these things,

11:26.040 --> 11:30.240
Even they shall understand the loving kindness of the Lord.

11:32.140 --> 11:33.300
Psalm 108

11:33.940 --> 11:36.320
O God, my heart is fixed,

11:36.600 --> 11:40.460
I will sing and give praise even with my glory.

11:41.240 --> 11:43.060
Awake, sultry and harp,

11:43.440 --> 11:45.680
I myself will awake early.

11:46.180 --> 11:49.300
I will praise thee, O Lord, among the people,

11:49.300 --> 11:53.380
And I will sing praises unto thee among the nations.

11:54.020 --> 11:56.820
For thy mercy is great above the heavens,

11:57.400 --> 12:00.760
And thy truth reacheth unto the clouds.

12:01.660 --> 12:04.440
Be thou exalted, O God, above the heavens,

12:05.100 --> 12:07.860
And thy glory above all the earth,

12:08.600 --> 12:10.880
That thy beloved may be delivered,

12:11.640 --> 12:14.340
Save with thy right hand and answer me.

12:15.560 --> 12:17.720
God hath spoken in his holiness,

12:17.720 --> 12:21.140
I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem,

12:21.700 --> 12:24.140
And meet out the valley of Sukkoth.

12:25.100 --> 12:28.100
Gilead is mine, Manasseh is mine,

12:28.460 --> 12:32.020
Ephraim also is the strength of mine head,

12:32.440 --> 12:34.280
Judah is my law-giver,

12:34.900 --> 12:36.820
Moab is my wash-pot,

12:37.460 --> 12:40.660
Over Edom will I cast out my shoe,

12:41.100 --> 12:43.280
Over Philistia will I triumph.

12:44.040 --> 12:46.580
Who will bring me into the strong city?

12:47.180 --> 12:49.560
Who will lead me into Edom?

12:50.660 --> 12:53.900
Wilt not thou, O God, who hast cast us off,

12:54.200 --> 12:58.120
And wilt not thou, O God, go forth with our hosts?

12:59.620 --> 13:01.160
Give us help from trouble,

13:01.860 --> 13:04.300
For vain is the help of man.

13:05.480 --> 13:07.740
Through God we shall do valiantly,

13:08.300 --> 13:12.120
For he it is that shall tread down our enemies.

13:13.760 --> 13:15.200
Psalm 109

13:15.200 --> 13:19.580
Hold not thy peace, O God, of my praise,

13:20.540 --> 13:24.320
For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful

13:24.320 --> 13:26.040
Are opened against me.

13:26.620 --> 13:30.000
They have spoken against me with a lying tongue.

13:30.860 --> 13:34.500
They compassed me about also with words of hatred,

13:35.260 --> 13:37.760
And fought against me without a cause.

13:39.080 --> 13:41.800
For my love they are my adversaries,

13:41.800 --> 13:44.800
But I give myself unto prayer,

13:45.420 --> 13:50.040
And they have rewarded me evil for good and hatred for my love.

13:51.120 --> 13:53.140
Set thou a wicked man over him,

13:53.880 --> 13:56.720
And let Satan stand at his right hand.

13:57.660 --> 14:00.460
When he shall be judged let him be condemned,

14:01.340 --> 14:03.540
And let his prayer become sin.

14:04.320 --> 14:05.960
Let his days be few,

14:06.380 --> 14:08.400
And let another take his office.

14:09.040 --> 14:11.360
Let his children be fatherless,

14:11.800 --> 14:13.380
And his wife a widow.

14:14.360 --> 14:18.520
Let his children be continually vagabonds and beg.

14:19.140 --> 14:23.320
Let them seek their bread also out of their desolate places.

14:24.600 --> 14:28.020
Let the extortioner catch all that he hath,

14:28.880 --> 14:31.940
And let the stranger spoil his labor.

14:33.080 --> 14:36.340
Let there be none to extend mercy unto him,

14:36.540 --> 14:40.220
Neither let there be any to favor his fatherless children.

14:40.780 --> 14:43.440
Let his posterity be cut off,

14:43.680 --> 14:48.240
And in the generation following let their name be blotted out.

14:49.540 --> 14:53.840
Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered with the Lord,

14:54.520 --> 14:57.780
And let not the sin of his mother be blotted out.

14:58.320 --> 15:00.980
Let them be before the Lord continually,

15:01.540 --> 15:04.800
That he may cut off the memory of them from the earth,

15:05.060 --> 15:08.120
Because that he remembered not to show mercy,

15:08.120 --> 15:11.640
But persecuted the poor and needy man,

15:12.160 --> 15:15.320
That he might even slay the broken in heart.

15:16.720 --> 15:17.960
As he loved cursing,

15:18.860 --> 15:20.460
So let it come unto him.

15:20.820 --> 15:22.660
As he delighted not in blessing,

15:23.500 --> 15:25.480
So let it be far from him.

15:26.500 --> 15:30.460
As he clothed himself with cursing like as with his garment,

15:30.920 --> 15:34.240
So let it come into his bowels like water,

15:34.620 --> 15:36.840
And like oil into his bones.

15:38.120 --> 15:41.440
Let it be unto him as the garment which covereth him,

15:41.960 --> 15:45.500
And for a girdle wherewith he is girded continually.

15:46.500 --> 15:50.300
Let this be the reward of mine adversaries from the Lord,

15:50.940 --> 15:54.580
And of them that speak evil against my soul.

15:55.180 --> 15:59.140
But do thou for me, O God the Lord, for thy name's sake,

15:59.660 --> 16:02.720
Because thy mercy is good, deliver thou me.

16:03.340 --> 16:08.020
For I am poor and needy, and my heart is wounded within me.

16:08.900 --> 16:12.720
I am gone like the shadow when it declineeth,

16:13.020 --> 16:16.120
I am tossed up and down as the locust,

16:16.480 --> 16:19.360
My knees are weak through fasting,

16:20.340 --> 16:22.760
And my flesh faileth of fatness.

16:23.720 --> 16:26.420
I became also a reproach unto them,

16:26.880 --> 16:29.760
When they looked upon me they shaked their heads.

16:30.600 --> 16:32.560
Help me, O Lord my God,

16:32.940 --> 16:35.800
O save me according to thy mercy,

16:36.460 --> 16:40.220
That they may know that this is thy hand,

16:40.380 --> 16:42.480
That thou, Lord, hast done it.

16:43.380 --> 16:45.820
Let them curse, but bless thou.

16:46.760 --> 16:49.980
When they arise, let them be ashamed,

16:50.660 --> 16:52.720
But let thy servant rejoice.

16:53.820 --> 16:56.760
Let mine adversaries be clothed with shame,

16:57.860 --> 17:02.940
And let them cover themselves with their own confusion as with a mantle.

17:04.780 --> 17:08.340
I will greatly praise the Lord with my mouth,

17:08.620 --> 17:12.020
Yea, I will praise him among the multitude,

17:12.620 --> 17:15.700
For he shall stand at the right hand of the poor,

17:15.840 --> 17:20.040
To save him from those that condemn his soul.

17:23.100 --> 17:24.460
Psalm 110

17:25.480 --> 17:27.980
The Lord said unto my Lord,

17:28.460 --> 17:30.480
Sit thou at my right hand,

17:30.860 --> 17:32.920
Until I make thine enemies thy footstool,

17:33.760 --> 17:38.040
The Lord shall send the rod of thy strength out of Zion,

17:38.660 --> 17:41.380
Rule thou in the midst of thine enemies,

17:42.180 --> 17:45.120
Thy people shall be willing in the day of thy power,

17:45.540 --> 17:48.800
In the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning,

17:49.240 --> 17:51.180
Thou hast the dew of thy youth.

17:52.540 --> 17:55.400
The Lord hath sworn, and will not repent,

17:56.080 --> 17:59.600
Thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek.

17:59.600 --> 18:05.900
The Lord at thy right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath,

18:06.900 --> 18:08.840
He shall judge among the heathen,

18:09.100 --> 18:12.160
He shall fill the places with the dead bodies,

18:12.980 --> 18:15.900
He shall wound the heads over many countries,

18:17.020 --> 18:19.240
He shall drink of the brook in the way,

18:19.660 --> 18:21.760
Therefore shall he lift up the head.

18:24.720 --> 18:26.000
Psalm 111

18:26.000 --> 18:27.620
Praise ye the Lord,

18:27.620 --> 18:30.960
I will praise the Lord with my whole heart,

18:31.360 --> 18:34.660
In the assembly of the upright, and in the congregation.

18:35.580 --> 18:37.480
The works of the Lord are great,

18:38.000 --> 18:40.820
Sought out of all them that have pleasure therein.

18:41.320 --> 18:43.540
His work is honorable and glorious,

18:44.280 --> 18:46.600
And his righteousness endureth for ever.

18:47.420 --> 18:50.480
He hath made his wonderful works to be remembered.

18:51.840 --> 18:55.160
The Lord is gracious and full of compassion,

18:55.160 --> 18:58.460
He hath given meat unto them that fear him,

18:58.860 --> 19:01.540
He will ever be mindful of his covenant,

19:02.400 --> 19:05.860
He hath showed his people the power of his works,

19:06.420 --> 19:09.440
That he may give them the heritage of the heathen.

19:11.120 --> 19:15.080
The works of his hands are verity and judgment,

19:15.580 --> 19:17.640
All his commandments are sure,

19:18.140 --> 19:20.660
They stand fast for ever and ever,

19:20.940 --> 19:23.620
And are done in truth and uprightness.

19:24.300 --> 19:26.880
He sent redemption unto his people,

19:27.160 --> 19:29.940
He hath commanded his covenant for ever,

19:30.680 --> 19:33.140
Holy and reverend is his name.

19:34.000 --> 19:37.280
The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom,

19:38.060 --> 19:42.300
A good understanding have all they that do his commandments,

19:42.940 --> 19:45.360
His praise endureth for ever.

19:46.840 --> 19:48.360
Psalm 112

19:49.380 --> 19:51.060
Praise ye the Lord,

19:51.060 --> 19:54.800
Blessed is the man that feareth the Lord,

19:55.320 --> 19:57.640
That delighteth greatly in his commandments,

19:58.400 --> 20:01.320
His seed shall be mighty upon earth,

20:02.100 --> 20:05.120
The generation of the upright shall be blessed,

20:05.860 --> 20:08.940
Wealth and riches shall be in his house,

20:09.580 --> 20:12.120
And his righteousness endureth for ever.

20:13.060 --> 20:16.340
Unto the upright there ariseth light in the darkness,

20:17.000 --> 20:21.180
He is gracious and full of compassion and righteous,

20:22.340 --> 20:25.020
A good man showeth favor and lendeth,

20:25.700 --> 20:28.580
He will guide his affairs with discretion,

20:29.580 --> 20:32.360
Surely he shall not be moved for ever,

20:32.920 --> 20:36.460
The righteous shall be in everlasting remembrance,

20:36.880 --> 20:39.540
He shall not be afraid of evil tidings,

20:39.900 --> 20:42.960
His heart is fixed, trusting in the Lord,

20:43.460 --> 20:45.020
His heart is established,

20:45.020 --> 20:49.680
He shall not be afraid until he see his desire upon his enemies,

20:50.300 --> 20:53.900
He hath dispersed, he hath given to the poor,

20:54.360 --> 20:56.620
His righteousness endureth for ever,

20:57.100 --> 20:59.580
His horn shall be exalted with honor,

21:00.100 --> 21:02.700
The wicked shall see it and be grieved,

21:03.120 --> 21:06.940
He shall gnash with his teeth and melt away,

21:07.560 --> 21:10.460
The desire of the wicked shall perish.

21:11.280 --> 21:12.380
Psalm 113

21:13.080 --> 21:17.400
Praise ye the Lord, praise, O ye servants of the Lord,

21:17.780 --> 21:20.020
Praise the name of the Lord!

21:20.600 --> 21:22.560
Blessed be the name of the Lord,

21:23.160 --> 21:25.920
From this time forth and for evermore,

21:26.440 --> 21:29.200
From the rising of the sun unto the going down

21:29.200 --> 21:32.800
Of the same the Lord's name is to be praised.

21:33.760 --> 21:35.860
The Lord is high above all nations,

21:36.340 --> 21:38.700
And his glory above the heavens,

21:39.420 --> 21:42.040
Who is like unto the Lord our God,

21:42.240 --> 21:43.620
Who dwelleth on high,

21:44.300 --> 21:47.480
Who humbleth himself to behold the things

21:47.480 --> 21:49.880
That are in heaven and in the earth,

21:50.760 --> 21:53.460
He raiseth up the poor out of the dust,

21:53.920 --> 21:56.980
And lifteth the needy out of the dung-hill,

21:57.680 --> 21:59.760
That he may set him with princes,

22:00.300 --> 22:02.560
Even with the princes of his people,

22:03.460 --> 22:06.440
He maketh the barren woman to keep house,

22:07.060 --> 22:10.000
And to be a joyful mother of children.

22:10.580 --> 22:12.360
Praise ye the Lord!

22:12.840 --> 22:14.620
Psalm 114

22:14.620 --> 22:17.040
When Israel went out of Egypt,

22:17.400 --> 22:21.100
The house of Jacob from a people of strange language,

22:21.680 --> 22:23.300
Judah was his sanctuary,

22:23.700 --> 22:25.620
And Israel his dominion,

22:26.020 --> 22:27.500
The sea sawed and fled,

22:28.060 --> 22:29.800
Jordan was driven back,

22:30.280 --> 22:32.760
The mountains skipped like rams,

22:33.240 --> 22:35.160
And the little hills like lambs.

22:35.980 --> 22:39.520
What ailed thee, O thou sea, that thou flettest,

22:40.220 --> 22:44.120
Thou Jordan, that thou wast driven back,

22:45.160 --> 22:47.800
Ye mountains that ye skipped like rams,

22:48.060 --> 22:50.320
And ye little hills like lambs,

22:51.040 --> 22:54.180
Tremble thou earth at the presence of the Lord,

22:54.700 --> 22:57.000
At the presence of the God of Jacob,

22:57.660 --> 23:00.420
Which turned the rock into a standing water,

23:01.000 --> 23:04.060
The flint into a fountain of waters.

23:05.200 --> 23:06.520
Psalm 115

23:07.180 --> 23:10.620
Not unto us, O Lord, not unto us,

23:10.680 --> 23:12.880
But unto thy name give glory,

23:13.340 --> 23:16.020
For thy mercy and for thy truth's sake.

23:16.960 --> 23:18.680
Wherefore should the heathen say,

23:19.200 --> 23:20.860
Where is now their God?

23:21.820 --> 23:23.460
But our God is in the heavens,

23:23.880 --> 23:26.660
He hath done whatsoever he hath pleased.

23:27.760 --> 23:29.740
Their idols are silver and gold,

23:29.880 --> 23:31.560
The work of men's hands.

23:32.380 --> 23:34.940
They have mouths, but they speak not,

23:35.400 --> 23:38.460
Eyes have they, but they see not,

23:38.820 --> 23:41.600
They have ears, but they hear not,

23:42.340 --> 23:45.420
Noses have they, but they smell not,

23:46.000 --> 23:48.300
They have hands, but they handle not,

23:48.640 --> 23:51.340
Feet have they, but they walk not,

23:51.480 --> 23:54.000
Neither speak they through their throat.

23:54.800 --> 23:57.300
They that make them are like unto them,

23:58.020 --> 24:00.700
So is every one that trusteth in them.

24:01.340 --> 24:04.220
O Israel, trust thou in the Lord,

24:05.220 --> 24:07.640
He is their help and their shield.

24:08.440 --> 24:11.220
O house of Aaron, trust in the Lord,

24:11.720 --> 24:13.860
He is their help and their shield.

24:14.880 --> 24:18.220
Ye that fear the Lord, trust in the Lord,

24:18.440 --> 24:21.300
He is their help and their shield.

24:22.200 --> 24:24.500
The Lord hath been mindful of us,

24:24.700 --> 24:25.940
He will bless us,

24:26.140 --> 24:28.220
He will bless the house of Israel,

24:28.540 --> 24:30.560
He will bless the house of Aaron.

24:30.700 --> 24:33.340
He will bless them that fear the Lord,

24:33.520 --> 24:34.900
Both small and great,

24:35.540 --> 24:38.360
The Lord shall increase you more and more,

24:38.600 --> 24:40.000
You and your children.

24:41.420 --> 24:43.440
Ye are blessed of the Lord,

24:43.820 --> 24:45.280
Which made heaven and earth,

24:45.820 --> 24:48.380
The heaven, even the heavens are the Lord's,

24:49.180 --> 24:52.580
But the earth hath he given to the children of men.

24:53.580 --> 24:55.340
The dead praise not the Lord,

24:56.120 --> 24:58.720
Neither any that go down into silence,

24:59.300 --> 25:01.160
But we will bless the Lord,

25:01.380 --> 25:04.040
From this time forth and for evermore.

25:04.620 --> 25:05.820
Praise the Lord.

